智利人是世界上最大的麵包食者之一，僅次於德國人。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Tracey Chandler |title=Eat and drink like a Chilean |url=https://www.contactchile.cl/en/santiago-blog/eat-and-drink-like-a-chilean-20140901 |website=www.contactchile.cl |language=en |accessdate=2019-12-02 |archive-date=2019-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213230212/https://www.contactchile.cl/en/santiago-blog/eat-and-drink-like-a-chilean-20140901 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="FoddyChile">{{cite web |url=http://foodychile.com/2012/02/14/el-tamiz-bread-cheesecake-and-a-bit-of-variety |title=El Tamiz: Bread, cheesecake and a bit of variety |date=2012-02-14 |accessdate=2012-12-19 |work=foodychile.com |dead-status=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120706233016/http://foodychile.com/2012/02/14/el-tamiz-bread-cheesecake-and-a-bit-of-variety/ |archivedate=2012-07-06 }}</ref><ref name="Six Servings">{{cite web|url=http://www.sixservings.org/2010/10/bread-makes-the-world-go-round |title=Bread Makes the World Go Round |date=2010-10-15 |work=sixservings.org |dead-status=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130114151325/http://www.sixservings.org/2010/10/bread-makes-the-world-go-round/ |archivedate=2013-01-14 }}</ref><ref name="Fundi2">{{cite web|url=http://fundi2.com/2011/07/chilean-bread|title=Chilean Bread|date=2011-07-06|work=fundi2.com|access-date=2013-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150828215121/http://fundi2.com/2011/07/chilean-bread/|archive-date=2015-08-28|dead-status=yes}}</ref> 智利人在早餐，午餐（作為前菜或開胃菜），[[上午茶|上午茶]]或晚餐時吃麵包。 “上午茶”麵包應盡可能新鮮，最好從當地麵包店購買仍熱的麵包。

